Pune (/ˈpuːnə/ POO-nə, Marathi: [ˈpuɳe] ⓘ), previously spelled in English as Poona (the officialuntil 1978),[15][16] is a city in Maharashtra state in the Deccan plateau in Western India. It is the administrative headquarters of the Pune district, and of Pune division. According to the 2011 Census of India,
 Pune is the ninth-most populous city in India with a population of 3.1 million residents within the city limits, and has a population of 7.2 million residents in the metropolitan region, making it the eight-most populous metropolitan area in India. [17]
